The pupa shares the following features with those of Conchapelopia , Helopelopia , Coffmania and Metapelopia : thoracic horn with a plastron plate and a distinct corona, and thoracic comb absent or poorly developed. However, it is distinct in the abdominal segment VIII with three LS-setae ( Niitsuma 2007 ). In the latter four genera, even in the other members of Thienemannimyia group, the pupal abdomen possesses five LS-setae on the segment VIII ( Fittkau & Murray 1986 for Conchapelopia and Helopelopia ; Hazra & Chaudhuri 2000 , Niitsuma 2008 for Coffmania ;
Silva et al. 2014
for Metapelopia ).

Hypopygium
(

). T IX with 12–19, 15 posterior setae. Gonocoxite 130–160, 148 μm long, 1.7–2.2, 2.0 times as long as broad at middle. Gonostylus stout, relatively short, 81–103, 95 μm long.

Genitalia
(

). Sternite VIII with about 20–30 setae on each side. Notum 98–115 μm long. Segment X with 4–5 lateral setae. Labium with apical microtrichia. Seminal capsules oval, 60–64 μm long, 1.1–1.3 times as long as broad.

Hypopygium
(

). T IX with 11–16, 14 posterior setae. Gonocoxite 180–200, 190 μm long, and almost twice as long as broad at middle. Gonostylus 123–125, 124 μm long.

Genitalia
(

). Sternite VIII with about 30 setae on each side. Notum 160 μm long. Segment X with 3 lateral setae. Labium with apical microtrichia. Seminal capsules 60 μm long, 1.1 times as long as broad.

Hypopygium
(

). T IX with 16 posterior setae. Gonocoxite 197 μm long, and 2.2 times as long as broad at middle. Gonostylus stout, 130 μm long.

